=== pykrx BLOCKER — 2026-04-16 ===
STOP: KRX data API now requires user credentials. pykrx 1.0.51 (installed) cannot
authenticate to the updated KRX portal — all API calls return HTTP 400 "LOGOUT".
pykrx 1.2.7 (latest) added a login system requiring KRX_ID and KRX_PW env vars.

Root cause:
  - KRX changed data.krx.co.kr from anonymous to login-required access (sometime in 2025).
  - pykrx 1.0.51 makes unauthenticated POST calls; the KRX server responds "LOGOUT" (400).
  - pykrx 1.2.7 adds auth.py with build_krx_session() using KRX_ID/KRX_PW env vars.
  - Tunnel geo-block workaround is confirmed working (ipinfo returns country=KR).

Actions taken:
  - Tunnel smoke test: PASSED (Oracle Seoul VM, Chuncheon, KR — 168.107.3.138)
  - stage1_pull_pykrx.py refactored to use krx_tunnel() context manager correctly.
  - Confirmed pykrx 1.0.51 fails with HTTP 400 "LOGOUT" on all KRX API endpoints.
  - Confirmed pykrx 1.2.7 requires KRX_ID + KRX_PW credentials.

User action required:
  1. Register at https://data.krx.co.kr and obtain a login (KRX_ID / KRX_PW).
  2. Add KRX_ID and KRX_PW to the project .env file.
  3. Allow upgrade to pykrx==1.2.7 (per constraints, package install requires explicit approval
     and version logging to logs/stage_-1_env.log).
  4. If credentials are not available, identify an alternative KR equity data source
     (e.g., FinanceDataReader, DART API, or a cached dataset).
